config.editorData:
The Summary table works in 2 steps.
First across time, then across VMs.

In the first step, each VM is measured across time. It calculates the VM memory contention (%) at the 99th percentile of the reporting period. For example, if there are 100 data points, it takes the 99th worst data.

In the second step, it takes the average of all VMs. As a leading indicator, it also takes the worst of all these 99th percentile data.
config.title: Explanation

dashboards.description:
Part of a report covering capacity. Designed to be run on a weekly basis, and be compared with previous week result. 
Working with a VCF expert, tailor the dashboard and widget to the specific requirements.

The color in the Time Remaining widget reflects the number of days before the datastore will run out of capacity.

The size of each square on the heat map datastore reflects the relative size of the datastore actual size. Larger datastore is shown larger.
